## 2. `df_question_nodes.csv` — Reasoning Archetype Mappings

Maps each question to its constituent reasoning nodes (micro-skills). One question maps to 1–3 nodes. This is the "Question DNA" — the atomic skills required to solve each question.

**Rows:** 5,150 | **Unique nodes:** 362 | **Relationship:** Many-to-many (question ↔ node)

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `question_id` | string | Foreign key → `df_master.question_id` |
| `node_id` | string | Unique node identifier. Format: `N_M_{topic_num}_{seq}` |
| `node_name` | string | Human-readable node name (e.g., "Log-equation-to-polynomial reduction") |
| `cognitive_operation` | string | Detailed description of the cognitive work required. 1–3 sentences explaining what the student must do |
| `cognitive_demand` | string | Complexity tier from the 5-level demand spectrum |
| `reasoning` | string | Why this demand level was assigned. Explains the cognitive load breakdown |

**Cognitive demand values (ascending complexity):**

| Level | Meaning | Example |
|-------|---------|---------|
| Direct Application | Plug values into a known formula | Evaluate a definite integral using a standard result |
| Formula with Judgment | Choose the right formula, then apply | Decide between integration by parts vs. substitution |
| Build Then Solve | Construct the mathematical setup from scratch | Translate a word problem into a system of equations |
| Build and Work Backwards | Forward setup + backward verification | Solve, then eliminate extraneous solutions |
| Reverse Engineer | Deduce conditions from a given result | Given the answer is 7, find the parameter value |

Some questions receive transitional labels (e.g., "Formula with Judgment to Build Then Solve") when they sit between tiers.

**Sample row:**
```
question_id: Q_M_15_001
node_id: N_M_16_003
node_name: Log-equation-to-polynomial reduction
cognitive_operation: "Convert a logarithmic equation into a polynomial..."
cognitive_demand: Formula with Judgment
reasoning: "The student must recall log/exponential identities but the main cognitive work is determining which substitution..."
```

