## 6. `prerequisite_final.json` — Foundational Skills

42 below-syllabus cognitive skills that are never explicitly taught but cause correlated failures across unrelated topics. Used by F10 (Foundational Skill Hypothesis) to detect root causes that topic-level analysis misses.

**Count:** 42 skills (F001–F042)

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `skill_id` | string | Unique ID (F001–F042) |
| `skill_name` | string | Concise skill name (e.g., "Translating verbal or geometric constraints into equations") |
| `description` | string | What the skill involves, in 2–3 sentences |
| `why_foundational` | string | Why this skill isn't covered by topic-level analysis |
| `failure_signature` | string | Observable pattern when a student lacks this skill |
| `dependent_topics` | list of objects | Topics that rely on this skill, each with `topic` and `how_it_manifests` |
| `diagnostic_question_idea` | string | A single question that would test this specific skill in isolation |

**Sample entry (abbreviated):**
```json
{
  "skill_id": "F001",
  "skill_name": "Translating verbal or geometric constraints into equations",
  "description": "The student can read a problem stated in words or geometry and produce the algebraic equation...",
  "failure_signature": "The student stalls at the first line of algebra...",
  "dependent_topics": [
    {"topic": "Application Of Derivatives", "how_it_manifests": "Optimization problems..."},
    {"topic": "Differential Equations", "how_it_manifests": "..."}
  ],
  "diagnostic_question_idea": "A rectangular box with no lid is made from 12 m² of cardboard..."
}
```

