## 7. `student_responses` — Student Test Data (Synthetic)

Generated per-student. Each row is one question attempt. The prototype generates 5 synthetic students × 15 tests × ~25 questions per test.

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `student_id` | string | Student identifier (e.g., "PRIYA", "ARJUN") |
| `question_id` | string | Foreign key → `df_master.question_id` |
| `is_correct` | boolean | Whether the student answered correctly |
| `time_taken_seconds` | integer | Time spent on this question |
| `confidence_rating` | integer | Student's self-reported confidence (1 = low, 2 = medium, 3 = high) |
| `test_timestamp` | datetime | When the test was taken (used for temporal analysis in F11) |

## 8. `test_composition` — Test Structure (Synthetic)

Lists all questions assigned to each test, including unattempted ones. Required by F15 (Time ROI) to calculate time allocation efficiency.

| Column | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `student_id` | string | Student identifier |
| `test_timestamp` | datetime | Matches timestamps in `student_responses` |
| `question_id` | string | Foreign key → `df_master.question_id` |

